Name: HCPV Module

Caption.String: 2. The reference selection determines the maximum power value shown above.
3. Efficiency values are for beam irradiance (W/m2).
1. Radiation levels must increase monotonically, but not necessarily in even increments.

The cell temperature coefficients a, b, and dT are empirically determined from test data.  In the absence of measured data for a particular concentrator module, it is recommended to use the default values.
Maximum power depends on the reference beam normal irradiance (DNI) and efficiency values specified below assuming an ambient temperature of 20 deg celsius, a wind speed of 4 m/s, and air mass 1.5.

hcpv.module.cell_temp.Label: Estimated cell temperature at reference conditions

module_a.Label: Estimated upper limit at high irradiance and low wind speed (a)

module_b.Label: Rate at which module temperature drops as wind speed increases (b)

module_dT.Label: Temperature difference between heat sink and cell at reference conditions (dT)

Callbacks: MAM[i] = a0 + a1*AM + a2*pow(AM,2) + a3*pow(AM,3) + a4*pow(AM,4);
